The paper presents a novel Gaussian latent variable model for dimensionality reduction on Riemannian manifolds, which is a topic related to machine learning and computer vision. The paper also discusses the application of the model in clustering and statistical shape analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence, statistics, and numerical analysis.
